# Documentation Standards

## MDX Format

### Basic Structure

```mdx
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "Page description"
---

## Section

Content here.

<CardGroup cols={2}>
  <Card title="Card Title" icon="icon-name" href="/link">
    Card description
  </Card>
</CardGroup>
```

## MDX Components

### Cards

```mdx
<Card title="Title" icon="icon-name" href="/link">
  Description
</Card>

<CardGroup cols={2}>
  <Card title="Card 1" icon="icon1" />
  <Card title="Card 2" icon="icon2" />
</CardGroup>
```

### Code Blocks

```mdx
```python
def example():
    pass
```

### Tabs

```mdx
<Tabs>
  <Tab title="Tab 1" icon="icon1">
    Content 1
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="Tab 2" icon="icon2">
    Content 2
  </Tab>
</Tabs>
```

### Steps

```mdx
<Steps>
  <Step title="Step 1" icon="icon1">
    Step description
  </Step>
  <Step title="Step 2" icon="icon2">
    Step description
  </Step>
</Steps>
```

### Alerts

```mdx
<Info>
  Informational message
</Info>

<Warning>
  Warning message
</Warning>

<Tip>
  Tip message
</Tip>

<Note>
  Note message
</Note>
```

### Accordions

```mdx
<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Title" icon="icon">
    Content
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>
```

## API Documentation

### Endpoint Documentation

```mdx
## Endpoint Name

#### `GET /v1/resource`

Get resource description.

**Query Parameters**:
- `limit` (int): Number of results (default: 25)
- `offset` (int): Pagination offset

**Returns**: List of resource objects

**Example**:
```bash
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer token" \
  https://api.omi.me/v1/resource?limit=10
```
```

## Mermaid Diagrams

### Flowchart

```mdx
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B[Process]
    B --> C[End]
```
```

### Sequence Diagram

```mdx
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A
    participant B
    A->>B: Message
    B-->>A: Response
```
```

## Best Practices

1. **Clear Titles**: Use descriptive page titles
2. **Structure**: Use consistent heading hierarchy
3. **Examples**: Include code examples
4. **Diagrams**: Use Mermaid for complex flows
5. **Links**: Link to related documentation
6. **Components**: Use MDX components for better UX
7. **Updates**: Keep docs in sync with code

